ZH: 肝脏是人体重要的器官之一。
EN: The liver is one of the important organs in the human body.

ZH: 吸烟会损害肝脏健康。
EN: Smoking can harm the health of the liver.

ZH: 饮酒过量会对肝脏造成伤害。
EN: Excessive alcohol consumption can harm the liver.

ZH: 肝脏功能不好会影响消化吸收。
EN: Poor liver function can affect digestion and absorption.

ZH: 多吃水果蔬菜有益于肝脏健康。
EN: Eating more fruits and vegetables is beneficial to liver health.

ZH: 运动可以加强肝脏的代谢功能。
EN: Exercise can strengthen the metabolic function of the liver.

ZH: 肝脏疾病可能导致黄疸。
EN: Liver disease can lead to jaundice.

ZH: 肝脏功能异常可引起黏膜出血。
EN: Abnormal liver function can cause mucous membrane bleeding.

ZH: 肝脏炎症可能导致肝硬化。
EN: Inflammation of the liver can lead to cirrhosis.

ZH: 肝脏癌症是一种致命的疾病。
EN: Liver cancer is a deadly disease.

ZH: 红糖水可以帮助保护肝脏。
EN: Brown sugar water can help protect the liver.

ZH: 肝脏损伤会影响体内毒素代谢。
EN: Liver damage can affect the metabolism of toxins in the body.

ZH: 肝脏功能紊乱可能导致体液潴留。
EN: Disruption of liver function can lead to fluid retention in the body.

ZH: 肝脏是排毒器官之一。
EN: The liver is one of the detoxification organs.

ZH: 慢性肝炎可能导致肝硬化。
EN: Chronic hepatitis can lead to cirrhosis of the liver.

ZH: 肝脏是脂肪代谢的关键器官之一。
EN: The liver is one of the key organs for fat metabolism.

ZH: 饮酒对肝脏有害。
EN: Drinking alcohol is harmful to the liver.

ZH: 吃清淡食物有利于肝脏健康。
EN: Eating light foods is beneficial to liver health.

ZH: 肝脏是人体的化学实验室。
EN: The liver is the chemical laboratory of the human body.

ZH: 肝脏疾病会对身体造成严重危害。
EN: Liver disease can cause serious harm to the body.
